LECTURE: The Conditional (Ternary) Operator

  (Boolean value) ? (if true) : (else false)

1. If your country's population is greater than 33 million, use the ternary operator
to log a string like this to the console: 'Portugal's population is above average'.
Otherwise, simply log 'Portugal's population is below average'. Notice how only
one word changes between these two sentences!
2. After checking the result, change the population temporarily to 13 and then to
130. See the different results, and set the population back to original
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

const population = 120;

population >= 33 ? console.log("Your country population is above average") : console.log('Your country population is below average');

.................................................................................................
Your country population is above average

